display="inline"><![CDATA[A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be a local homomorphism, and suppose that the residue extension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(B)/k(A)]]></fr:tex> is trivial, with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(A)]]></fr:tex> algebraically closed.
    In order for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B/A]]></fr:tex> to be unramified, it is necessary and sufficient that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {B}]]></fr:tex> be (as an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {A}]]></fr:tex>-algebra) a quotient of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {A}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
